# High-Priority Rules
- Do exactly what was requested. Nothing extra.
- Keep changes minimal and local.
- Do not add files, dependencies, or abstractions unless strictly necessary.
- Do not refactor unrelated code.
- Keep domain logic separate from UI.
- Keep field names consistent everywhere.
- Do not hallucinate files, imports, APIs, or infrastructure.
- Prefer simple, boring solutions.
- Keep the product mobile-first, short-form, and practical.

## Living docs & alignment
- **[AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md)**, **[CLAUDE.md](../../CLAUDE.md)**, **[ARCHITECTURE.md](../../ARCHITECTURE.md)**, **ScopeLock-Project-Rules.mdc**, and **this file** are **living documents**. After **substantive code changes**, update affected docs so they stay accurate.
- When changing rules in **any** of those files, **compare the same topic in the others** and **keep them aligned** (especially CSS co-location, HTML/`esc()` rules, architecture/deployment constraints, and minimal-diff discipline).
- If a rule is meant to be global, mirror it across the shared rule files or replace duplication with a single explicit pointer.
- **Public branding:** Use **IronWork** in user-facing copy and product prose. Legacy internal identifiers, repo paths, storage keys, and factual filenames such as **`ScopeLock-Project-Rules.mdc`** may remain when renaming would risk breakage or make the reference inaccurate.
- **DocuSeal / e-sign:** Server env on the **running** process (not only `VITE_*` at build); validate webhooks and notification email on the **deployed** URL when checking production parity — **ARCHITECTURE.md** (*E-sign*) and **AGENTS.md**.
- **Invoice lifecycle:** No row → `Invoice`, `issued_at = null` → `Draft`, `issued_at != null` → `Invoiced` (payment-link creation sets `issued_at`). `payment_status`/`paid_at` set by Stripe webhook. No invoice e-sign tracking. **`InvoiceFinalPage`** refetches the invoice once on mount.
- **E-sign UI:** No interval polling; WO/CO detail sync status on open (plus send/resend refreshes).
- **Invoice issuance gate:** Invoice issuance (payment-link creation and send) is blocked until the parent work order is signature-satisfied (DocuSeal `completed` or `offline_signed_at` set). Invoice drafts can be created regardless of signature state.

## CSS (mandatory)
- Co-locate styles: `ComponentName.tsx` + `ComponentName.css`; owner imports its own CSS.
- **`App.css` only** for tokens, shell/layout, **shared** utilities, print/PDF globals—**not** for one page, wizard, or feature.
- **Do not** add new page/feature-specific styles to `App.css`. New pages and major components **must** ship with a paired CSS file.

## HTML strings (mandatory)
- User-controlled text interpolated into generated HTML strings must use `esc()` from `src/lib/html-escape.ts`.
